Business Brief -- Columbia Gas System Inc.:
   Natural Gas Concern Posts
   34% Rise in 4th-Period Net
The fourth quarter excluded $31 million of after-tax
interest expense on pre-bankruptcy debt.
   For the year, the company reported a net loss of $694.4
million or $13.74 a share, compared with year-earlier net
income of $104.7 million or $2.21 a share. The losses were
related to charges associated with above-market-priced gas
purchase contracts. The contracts caused Columbia to file for
protection under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy code
last year.
   Revenue was up 9%, to $2.58 billion from $2.36 billion.